commit.message:
Update license file

It appears the license file (LGPL 2.0) is outdated as the top of the
main source code file, testbench.c, clearly says it's licensed under
LGPL 2.1.  Updated the license file to match.

better screenshot, gitignore update

- Remove margins around the screenshot.
- Add .DS_Store file to .gitignore.

v0.1.3, better documentation, remove CVS files

* Remove CVS directories and contents.  These are remnants from
  SDL_Pango, when its primary repository was on Sourceforge in CVS.
* Better documentation for SDL2_Pango.
* Increment version to 0.1.3.

Fix clang warnings

- Handle line enums defined in newer versions of Pango.
- Properly convert alignment enums from Pango to SDL2_Pango.

crash fix, cleanup warnings

- Cleanup various warnings.
- Explicitly return the result in SDLPango_CreateContext().  It appears
  this function implicitly returns the last function call's value on some
  platforms (e.g., on Ubuntu Linux with gcc) but not on other platforms
  (e.g., macOS with clang) where an invalid pointer can be returned and
  cause the caller to segfault.

Migrate test code to SDL2

- Migrate testbench.c to SDL2 and SDL2_Pango.
- Migrate autoconf/automake to SDL2 and SDL2_Pango.
- Commit autoconf/automake generated files to the repo.
- Fixed a typo in a defined constant name in testbench.c.

commit.message:
Update for newer versions of autotools

Updated to work with the following versons of autotools:

- autoconf 2.71
- automake 1.16.4
- libtool 2.4.6

Also generated configure, Makefile.in, and other required files so the
package is ready to be built.

Initial commit

Using the SDL2_Pango fork by Pere Pujal i Carabantes found at:

  https://sourceforge.net/projects/tuxpaint-sdl2/files/SDL2_Pango/SDL2_Pango-0.1.2.tar.gz/download
